---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const pressReleases = [
  {
    title: 'Gladiator Games Introduces Family-Friendly Membership Plans for All Ages',
    date: '2025',
    datePublished: '2025-01-14T10:00:00-06:00',
    dateModified: '2025-01-14T10:00:00-06:00',
    excerpt: 'Jefferson City\'s premier gaming center launches new tiered family membership pricing, making unlimited gaming more accessible for families with special rates for children and teens.',
    content: `Gladiator Games is proud to announce the launch of new family-friendly membership plans designed to make gaming more accessible and affordable for families throughout Central Missouri.

The new tiered pricing structure offers unlimited gaming access at rates tailored to different age groups:
• Adults (17+): $32 per month
• Teens (16 and under): $16 per month
• Children (8 and under): $8 per month

"We've listened to feedback from our community, and families told us they wanted an affordable way to enjoy gaming together," said the Gladiator Games team. "These new family plans make it possible for entire families to have unlimited access to our facility at prices that work for every budget."

The family membership plans include all the benefits of standard unlimited memberships, including access to over 100 games, professional gaming equipment with NVIDIA RTX 4060 graphics cards and high-refresh monitors, and participation in community events and tournaments.

"Gaming is for everyone, and we want to ensure that kids, teens, and adults can all experience the joy of competitive and casual gaming in a safe, welcoming environment," the team added. "Whether it's parents and kids playing together or teens competing with friends, these plans make it easy for families to make Gladiator Games part of their regular routine."

The family plans are particularly popular for:
• After-school gaming for students
• Weekend family gaming sessions
• Birthday celebration prep and practice
• Summer break entertainment

Parents appreciate the supervised environment, age-appropriate game options, and the ability to enjoy Strikers' restaurant and bowling while kids game. The facility maintains a family-friendly atmosphere suitable for all ages.

Family memberships are now available for sign-up at Gladiator Games inside Strikers Entertainment Center in Jefferson City. For more information about family plans, membership benefits, or to sign up, visit gladiatorgames.net or call (573) 338-1481.`,
  },
  {
    title: 'Gladiator Games Adds Popular Party Game "RV There Yet" to Gaming Library',
    date: '2025',
    datePublished: '2025-01-10T09:00:00-06:00',
    dateModified: '2025-01-10T09:00:00-06:00',
    excerpt: 'Jefferson City\'s premier gaming center expands its entertainment offerings with the addition of "RV There Yet" - the hilarious multiplayer party game that\'s taking the gaming community by storm.',
    content: `Gladiator Games is excited to announce the addition of "RV There Yet" to its extensive gaming library, bringing one of the most requested party games to Central Missouri gamers.

"RV There Yet" is a chaotic multiplayer party game that has quickly become a fan favorite for its accessible gameplay and laugh-out-loud moments. The game is perfect for groups, parties, and casual gaming sessions, making it an ideal addition to Gladiator Games' diverse game selection.

"We listen to our community, and 'RV There Yet' was one of the most requested titles," said the Gladiator Games team. "It's the perfect game for birthday parties, bachelor/bachelorette parties, and group events. We're thrilled to bring this experience to our guests."

The game joins Gladiator Games' library of over 100 titles, which spans competitive esports games, popular multiplayer titles, and party games suitable for all ages. The addition further solidifies Gladiator Games' position as Central Missouri's most comprehensive gaming destination.

"RV There Yet" is now available to play at all Gladiator Games stations. The center continues to regularly update its game library based on community feedback and the latest gaming releases.

Gladiator Games is open seven days a week at Strikers Entertainment Center in Jefferson City. For more information about available games and party packages, visit gladiatorgames.net or call (573) 338-1481.`,
  },
  {
    title: 'Gladiator Games Announces Move to Strikers Entertainment Center in Jefferson City',
    date: '2024',
    datePublished: '2024-11-01T10:00:00-06:00',
    dateModified: '2024-11-01T10:00:00-06:00',
    excerpt: 'Central Missouri\'s premier gaming destination finds its new home inside Strikers bowling and entertainment complex, creating Jefferson City\'s ultimate entertainment hub.',
    content: `Gladiator Games is excited to announce its relocation to Strikers Entertainment Center in Jefferson City, Missouri, bringing together gaming, bowling, dining, and arcade entertainment under one roof.

The strategic move positions Gladiator Games inside one of Jefferson City's most popular entertainment venues, creating a comprehensive destination for families, groups, and gaming enthusiasts. The new location offers convenient access, ample parking, and the ability to combine gaming with other entertainment options.

"Moving into Strikers Entertainment Center is a game-changer for us and our community," said the Gladiator Games team. "Now, families can enjoy bowling, grab a meal at Strikers' restaurant, visit the arcade, and experience our premium gaming center—all in one visit. It's the ultimate entertainment experience."

The partnership with Strikers allows Gladiator Games to offer enhanced services including full food and beverage delivery to gaming stations, party packages that combine bowling and gaming, and access to Strikers' full bar for adult gaming events.

Located inside the Strikers building, Gladiator Games is accessible by entering through the main Strikers entrance and heading down the stairs on the right. The gaming center maintains over 100 professional gaming stations equipped with NVIDIA RTX 4060 graphics cards, Intel Core i5-12600K processors, and high-refresh monitors.

"This location perfectly aligns with our mission to unite gamers and create thriving communities," the team added. "We're not just a gaming center anymore—we're part of Jefferson City's premier entertainment destination."

The gaming center is now open at its new location inside Strikers Entertainment Center. Walk-ins are welcome, or guests can call ahead at (573) 338-1481 to reserve gaming time or book parties. Visit gladiatorgames.net for directions, hours, and more information.`,
  },
  {
    title: 'Gladiator Games Opens Premier Gaming Center in Jefferson City, Missouri',
    date: '2024',
    datePublished: '2024-10-15T10:00:00-06:00',
    dateModified: '2024-10-15T10:00:00-06:00',
    excerpt: 'Gladiator Games, Jefferson City\'s newest competitive gaming destination, is now open inside Strikers Entertainment Center. The facility features 100+ gaming stations equipped with professional-grade hardware including NVIDIA RTX 4060 graphics cards, Intel Core i5-12600K processors, and high-refresh monitors.',
    content: `Gladiator Games is proud to announce the opening of Central Missouri's premier competitive gaming center, located inside Strikers Entertainment Center in Jefferson City, MO. The facility offers gamers of all skill levels access to professional-grade gaming equipment and a welcoming community environment.

The gaming center features over 100 gaming stations, each equipped with high-performance PCs featuring NVIDIA GeForce RTX 4060 graphics cards, 12th generation Intel Core i5-12600K processors, 32GB RAM, and high-refresh gaming monitors. The center maintains a typical network latency of 24ms, ensuring responsive gameplay for competitive titles.

"Our mission is to unite gamers and create thriving, meaningful communities," said the Gladiator Games team. "We're providing every gamer with the ultimate battleground—premium equipment, unbeatable performance, and a community where skill meets opportunity."

Gladiator Games offers flexible pricing options including $10/hour walk-in rates, $20 all-day passes, and unlimited monthly memberships starting at $16/month. The center is open seven days a week with extended hours on weekends.

In addition to open gaming, Gladiator Games hosts tournaments, LAN parties, birthday parties, corporate team-building events, and bachelor/bachelorette parties. The facility also offers private party rooms and custom tournament hosting services.

For more information, visit gladiatorgames.net or contact the center at (573) 338-1481.`,
  },
  {
    title: 'Gladiator Games Announces Tournament Series for Competitive Gamers',
    date: '2024',
    datePublished: '2024-10-20T10:00:00-06:00',
    dateModified: '2024-10-20T10:00:00-06:00',
    excerpt: 'The Jefferson City gaming center plans to host regular tournaments for popular competitive titles including Super Smash Bros, Rocket League, and League of Legends, with prizes and professional tournament management.',
    content: `Gladiator Games is launching a tournament series designed to bring competitive gaming to Central Missouri. The planned events will feature popular esports titles and provide local gamers with opportunities to compete for prizes and recognition.

Initial tournament offerings will include Super Smash Bros, Rocket League, and League of Legends competitions. Each tournament will feature professional bracket management, dedicated tournament staff, and prize pools.

"We want to create opportunities for competitive players in our region," explained the tournament coordinator. "Whether you're a seasoned competitor or trying tournaments for the first time, we'll provide a professional, welcoming environment."

The facility offers full tournament hosting services including registration management, bracket organization, streaming capabilities, and spectator viewing areas. Organizations and groups interested in hosting their own tournaments can contact Gladiator Games for custom packages.

Tournament dates and registration information will be announced on the Gladiator Games website and Discord server.`,
  },
  {
    title: 'Gaming Center Partners with Local Businesses to Support Jefferson City Community',
    date: '2024',
    datePublished: '2024-11-15T10:00:00-06:00',
    dateModified: '2024-11-15T10:00:00-06:00',
    excerpt: 'Gladiator Games collaborates with Strikers Entertainment Center and other local businesses to create a comprehensive entertainment destination for Jefferson City residents and visitors.',
    content: `Gladiator Games has formed strategic partnerships with local Jefferson City businesses to enhance the gaming experience and support the local community.

Located inside Strikers Entertainment Center, Gladiator Games guests have access to bowling, arcade games, and full food and beverage service from Strikers' restaurant and bar. This partnership creates a complete entertainment destination where families and groups can enjoy multiple activities in one location.

"The partnership with Strikers allows us to offer so much more than just gaming," noted the team. "Guests can enjoy a meal, bowl a few games, and settle in for a gaming session—all without leaving the building."

The gaming center also emphasizes supporting other local businesses and creating a positive impact in Jefferson City. Through corporate partnerships, school events, and community gatherings, Gladiator Games aims to be an active member of the Jefferson City community.

Gladiator Games is currently exploring additional partnerships with local schools, youth organizations, and businesses to expand gaming opportunities throughout Central Missouri.`,
  },
];
---

<Layout
  title="Press Releases - Gladiator Games"
  description="Latest news and press releases from Gladiator Games, Jefferson City's premier competitive gaming center and esports facility."
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    {pressReleases.map((release) => (
      <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
        "@context": "https://schema.org",
        "@type": "NewsArticle",
        "headline": release.title,
        "description": release.excerpt,
        "datePublished": release.datePublished,
        "dateModified": release.dateModified,
        "author": {
          "@type": "Organization",
          "name": "Gladiator Games",
          "url": "https://gladiatorgames.net"
        },
        "publisher": {
          "@type": "Organization",
          "name": "Gladiator Games",
          "url": "https://gladiatorgames.net",
          "logo": {
            "@type": "ImageObject",
            "url": "https://gladiatorgames.net/images/branding/logo-white.png"
          }
        },
        "mainEntityOfPage": {
          "@type": "WebPage",
          "@id": "https://gladiatorgames.net/press"
        }
      })} />
    ))}
  </Fragment>
  <Header />
  <main>
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="py-20 md:py-32 bg-brand-black">
      <div class="container-custom">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
          <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6 text-brand-white">
            Press & Media
          </h1>
          <p class="text-brand-gray text-lg mb-8">
            Latest news and announcements from Gladiator Games
          </p>
          <p class="text-brand-gray text-sm">
            For media inquiries, please contact us at <a href="mailto:contact@gladiatorgames.net" class="text-brand-orange hover:brightness-110">contact@gladiatorgames.net</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Press Releases -->
    <section class="py-16 bg-brand-black">
      <div class="container-custom">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-12">
          {pressReleases.map((release, index) => (
            <article class="card">
              <div class="mb-4">
                <time datetime={release.datePublished} class="text-brand-orange text-sm font-semibold">{release.date}</time>
                <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-brand-white mt-2 mb-4">
                  {release.title}
                </h2>
                <p class="text-brand-gray text-lg mb-6">
                  {release.excerpt}
                </p>
              </div>

              <details class="group">
                <summary class="cursor-pointer text-brand-orange hover:brightness-110 font-semibold flex items-center">
                  <span>Read Full Release</span>
                  <svg class="w-5 h-5 ml-2 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
                  </svg>
                </summary>
                <div class="mt-6 text-brand-gray space-y-4">
                  {release.content.split('\n\n').map(paragraph => (
                    <p>{paragraph}</p>
                  ))}
                </div>
              </details>

              {index < pressReleases.length - 1 && (
                <div class="mt-8 border-t border-brand-gray-dark"></div>
              )}
            </article>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Media Kit CTA -->
    <section class="py-16 bg-gradient-to-b from-brand-black to-brand-gray-dark">
      <div class="container-custom">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-brand-white">
            Need Media Resources?
          </h2>
          <p class="text-brand-gray text-lg mb-8">
            Access our complete media kit with logos, brand assets, and fact sheets
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
            <a href="/media-kit" class="btn-primary bg-brand-orange hover:bg-brand-orange-hover">
              View Media Kit
            </a>
            <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary bg-brand-cyan hover:bg-brand-purple">
              Contact Us
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
